title.narrative: Communications and media activities effectively promote child rights.

description.narrative: Despite the challenges presented by the COVID-19 pandemic, the media and external relations section continued its work to promote the rights of children in Madagascar, highlighting the obstacles to their realization, and the work of UNICEF and partners to address those challenges. While the section was restricted to tele-working for most of the year, media relations, trainings, digital production and events were produced at near normal levels, resulting in high visibility for the work on UNICEF, our partners and donors. The section supported global cause framework campaigns, extended work on youth advocacy, and organised high-profile events for World Children’s Day;(WCD).; | Status:Met | As-of Date:13/01/2021
